      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): support --file for image generate command",
        "body": "## Summary\nThe `image generate` CLI command was missing the `--file` option that `image edit` already supported. This PR adds `--file` support to achieve parity, forwarding input files to the image generation runtime.\n\nFixes #91734.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.ts`:\n  - Added `\"--file\"` to `image.generate` capability metadata flags\n  - Added `.option(\"--file <path>\", \"Input file\", collectOption, [])` to the `image generate` command registration\n  - Wired `opts.file` through to `runImageGenerate({ file: files })`\n\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts`:\n  - Added regression test: `forwards input files for image generate`\n  - Added regression test: `reports the expanded image.generate flags in capability inspect`\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm test src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts --run` — 97 passed\n- `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/cli/capability-cli.ts src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts` — clean\n- `pnpm build` — clean\n- `pnpm format:fix` — clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior addressed**: `openclaw infer image generate --file <path>` now accepts and forwards input files to the generation runtime, matching the existing `image edit --file` behavior.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux, Node.js 22, local source checkout.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `pnpm test src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts --run`\n- **Evidence after fix**: All 97 tests pass, including the two new regression tests that verify `--file` is accepted by the CLI parser and forwarded to `generateImage` as `inputImages`.\n- **Observed result after fix**: `image generate --file <path> --prompt \"...\"` correctly resolves the file and passes it to the runtime.\n- **What was not tested**: Live provider image generation with actual API keys; only CLI parsing and runtime forwarding is tested.",
